Title: The No-ghost Theorem for AdS_3 and the Stringy Exclusion Principle
Authors: J.M. Evans, M.R. Gaberdiel, M.J. Perry
Comments: 20 pages, LaTeX; references added
Report-no: DAMTP-98-37
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B535 (1998) 152-170
\\
  A complete proof of the No-ghost Theorem for bosonic and fermionic string
theories on AdS_3, or the group manifold of SU(1,1), is given. It is then shown
that the restriction on the spin (in terms of the level) that is necessary to
obtain a ghost-free spectrum corresponds to the stringy exclusion principle of
Maldacena and Strominger.
